---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import EmailSignup from "../components/EmailSignup.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Last Thread Co. is a short list of good things for the men in your life. Here's the story."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-olive">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-serif text-4xl text-ink sm:text-5xl">
      For the men who wear things out.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose-lt mt-10 space-y-6 text-ink/90">
      <p>
        Last Thread is a small editorial site about gifts for men. Not the
        kind of gifts that get unwrapped, admired for ten minutes, and then
        live in a drawer. The kind he'll actually use. The kind he'll wear
        until the elbows go through and then ask if you can find another one.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most of what we cover is unglamorous. Socks. Pocket knives. Cast iron.
        A flashlight small enough to clip to a keychain. The dopp kit he's
        been meaning to replace since his honeymoon. We try to write about
        each one the way a friend would tell you about it — with enough
        detail that you can tell whether it's right for him, and a sense of
        humor about the whole thing.
      </p>
      <p>
        We're not trying to teach you about "premium" anything. We're not
        going to use the word "curated" if we can help it. We're not going to
        tell you the watch costs three thousand dollars. We're going to tell
        you that the strap he's worn for ten years is finally cracked and
        here are three you could replace it with for the price of a tank of
        gas.
      </p>
      <p>
        A note about how this works: most of the product links on this site
        are affiliate links. If you buy something we recommend, we get a
        small commission. It doesn't cost you anything extra. We only link to
        things we'd give to our own dads, brothers, and husbands. If we
        wouldn't put one on the kitchen table at Christmas, it doesn't go on
        the site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Thanks for reading. If there's something you've been looking for and
        can't find a good version of, write to us — we read everything.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <EmailSignup
        heading="One good thing a week."
        subhead="Subscribe and we'll send the best things we've found, on Saturdays."
      />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-lt p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
</style>
